# sqlx embeds migration FILES at compile time and checksums their raw bytes;
# a database migrated by one build rejects another build if line endings
# differ ("migration N was previously applied but has been modified"). CI
# runners check out with core.autocrlf=true, so without this rule CI builds
# embed CRLF while local LF checkouts embed LF. Force LF everywhere so every
# build of the same commit embeds identical bytes. (The server also self-heals
# ending-only mismatches at startup; this rule stops creating them.)
*.sql text eol=lf

# Never let git touch binary assets.
*.dll binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
*.png binary
*.db binary
